The starch mogul system is a method of molding candy that allows runnier materials to be used than normal processes. The starch mogul system uses a machine with trays of starch. Each tray has a mold firmly pushed down in it to create cavities in the starch. The cavities are then filled with the candy material, and allowed to cool or harden as necessary. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Starch_mogul_system]
